    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To ensure safety, always verify that all base plates, sole boards, and ledgers are fully level on a solid foundation, especially when adjusting for wind or shifting ground. Check every frame for secure toe-nails, monitor the structural integrity of bracing and tie-ins, and confirm that all guardrails, mid-rails, and toe boards are installed and tight. Finally, inspect the platform surface to guarantee it is free from debris and obstacles that could destabilize loads.",
